<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: File_identification_arm  Entity: File  
   <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="File_identification_arm.File">
  A <b>File</b> is a file stored on a computer system or in
a stack of non-digital documents.
A <b>File</b> is either a
<express_ref
linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Hardcopy"/> 
or a 
<express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Digital_file"/>.  
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: File_identification_arm  Entity: File  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="File_identification_arm.File.id">
the identifier of the external file.
<example>
This attribute may be used to convey the identification of a digital file in the directory where it is stored.
</example>
        </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: File_identification_arm  Entity: File  Attribute: version 
   <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File.version"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="File_identification_arm.File.version">
a string that provides a version identifier for the file. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
        </ext_description>
				
<ext_description linkend="File_identification_arm.File.contained_data_type">
a string that provides information about the kind of data stored in the file. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
<p>Where applicable, the following values shall be used:</p>
<ul>
<li>'geometry': The file contains a shape model;</li>
<li>'NC data': The file contains numerical control data;</li>
<li>'FE data': The file contains finite element data;</li>
<li>'sample data': The file represents measured data;</li>
<li>'process plan': The document file represents process planning data;</li>
<li>'check plan': The document file represents quality control planning data;</li>
<li>'drawing': The document file represents a technical drawing.</li>
</ul>

        </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: File_identification_arm  Entity: Hardcopy  
   <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Hardcopy"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="File_identification_arm.Hardcopy">
  A <b>Hardcopy</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/> that represents a non-digital document.

   <example>
     An actual stack of paper 
     consisting of one or more sheets, on which some product data is written,
     printed or plotted. 
   </example>

      </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: File_identification_arm  Entity: Digital_file  
   <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Digital_file"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="File_identification_arm.Digital_file">
  A <b>Digital_file</b> is a type of 
<express_ref
  linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>. 
A <b>Digital_file</b> contains computer interpretable data and is stored on an electronic device.  
</ext_description>

<ext_description
linkend="File_identification_arm.File_location_identification">
A <b>File_location_identification</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="external_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_item_identification"/>
 that identifies the location of  
a <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>
 in an external storage system where it can be found.

<example number="1">
For a computer file identified by a filename and directory path, for
  example 'D:\project1\specification.txt', the
  <express_ref linkend="external_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_item_identification.external_id"/>

 attribute represents the filename, 
  'specification.txt' and the <express_ref linkend="external_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_source_identification.source_id"/>

 attribute represents the path
  name, 'D:\project1\'. 
</example>

<example number="2">
Examples of <express_ref linkend="external_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_source_identification.source_type"/>

 are:
<ul>
<li>'URL' - for a web page;</li> 
<li>'FTP' - for an FTP address;</li>
<li>'ISBN' - for physical documents.</li>
</ul>
</example>
</ext_description>

<ext_description
linkend="File_identification_arm.File_location_identification.wr:WR1">
The identified external item shall be of type <express_ref linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>.
</ext_description>

